  "text": "For recognition tasks, we commonly talk about ground-truth as the set of correct interpretations for a problem domain. However, in practice ground-truth is comprised of interpretations for a sample of a problem domain, produced by experts whose opinions may vary and even conflict [CITATION_1] . We propose that this type of ground-truth is more accurately understood as expert opinion, as suggested in this paper.",
